{"title":"Gallery: Victory for Lafay and the breakaway at the Giro d'Italia","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/9622/gallery-victory-for-lafay-and-the-breakaway-at-the-giro-ditalia","date":1621154023000,"content":"<span>\n      <span><a href=\"/authors/joe-robinson\">Joe Robinson</a></span>\n  </span><div>  \n  <div>      <div><span>16 May 2021</span></div>    </div></div><p>\nThe breakaway make it stick as young Lafay proves strongest on Stage 8</p>\n<div>\n      <p> The <a href=\"/tags/giro-ditalia\">Giro d'Italia</a> saw yet another breakaway success with young French climber Victor Lafay taking the win on Stage 8 to Guardia Sanframondi. </p>\n<p>The 25-year-old Cofidis rider proved the strongest from the day's nine-man break, ridinng the final 2.2km of the stage solo ahead of Francesco Gavazzi (Eolo-Kometa) and Nikias Arndt (<a href=\"/tags/team-dsm\">Team DSM</a>).</p>\n<p>Almost five minutes later, the main peloton of General Classification hopefuls crossed the line including Maglia Rosa wearer Attila Valter (<a href=\"/tags/groupama-fdj\">Groupama-FDJ</a>). The only GC riders to lose time were Jai Hindley (Team DSM) and Pello Bilbao (<a href=\"/tags/bahrain-victorious\">Bahrain Victorious</a>) who lost 11 seconds and 30 seconds respectively.</p>\n<div>      <div>See related </div>\n  \n  <div>      <div><a href=\"/in-depth/5405/blow-by-blow-inside-silca\">Blow by blow: inside Silca</a></div>      <div><a href=\"/reviews/5577/silca-grande-americano-seat-roll-review\">Silca Grande Americano Seat Roll review</a></div>      <div><a href=\"/garmin/9104/garmin-edge-1030-plus-gps-bike-computer-review\">Garmin Edge 1030 Plus GPS bike computer review</a></div>      <div><a href=\"/reviews/6361/wahoo-elemnt-roam-review-navigation-colour-screen-long-battery-life\">Wahoo Elemnt Roam long-term review</a></div>      <div><a href=\"/news/6463/cyclist-magazine-new-issue-on-sale-buy-it-now\">Cyclist magazine issue 113: on sale now!</a></div>    </div></div><p>\nIn other news, <a href=\"/tags/lotto-soudal\">Lotto-Soudal</a> sprinter Caleb Ewan abandoned mid-stage.</p>\n<p>Ahead of today's gravel mountain summit finish, here are Chris Auld's best images from Stage 8:</p>\n<p></p><div><div>\n  <a href=\"/in-depth/9621/giro-ditalia-2021-stage-8-gallery#3\"><p><span>Image 4 of</span> 20</p><img src=\"https://cdn2.cyclist.co.uk/sites/cyclist/files/styles/gallery_adv/public/2021/05/giro2021-stage8-4.jpg?itok=xxTM7KXk\" /></a></div>\n<p><span>Image 4 of </span>20</p>\n</div> <p></p>\n  </div>\n<div>  \n  <div>      <div>\n<div>\n\n          &lt;&gt;<span><a href=\"/in-depth/9621/giro-ditalia-2021-stage-8-gallery\">Giro d'Italia 2021 Stage 8 Gallery</a></span>&lt;/&gt;\n      \n  \n  <div>\n\n    \n    \n    <div><span>\n      <span><a href=\"/in-depth\">In-depth</a></span>\n  </span><div>  \n  <div>      <div><span>16 May 2021</span></div>    </div></div><div>\n        <div><ul><li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cyclist.co.uk%2Fin-depth%2F9621%2Fgiro-ditalia-2021-stage-8-gallery\">\r\n  <span>\r\n      \r\n          \r\n      \r\n  </span>\r\n  <span>facebook</span>\r\n</a>\r\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://twitter.com/home?status=Giro%20d%27Italia%202021%20Stage%208%20Gallery%20https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cyclist.co.uk%2Fin-depth%2F9621%2Fgiro-ditalia-2021-stage-8-gallery\">\r\n  <span>\r\n      \r\n      \r\n      \r\n  </span>\r\n  <span>twitter</span>\r\n</a>\r\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/share?url=Giro%20d%27Italia%202021%20Stage%208%20Gallery%20https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cyclist.co.uk%2Fin-depth%2F9621%2Fgiro-ditalia-2021-stage-8-gallery\">\r\n  <span>\r\n      \r\n          \r\n            \r\n              \r\n              \r\n            \r\n          \r\n      \r\n  </span>\r\n  <span>google+</span>\r\n</a>\r\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"mailto:?subject=Giro%20d%27Italia%202021%20Stage%208%20Gallery&amp;body=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cyclist.co.uk%2Fin-depth%2F9621%2Fgiro-ditalia-2021-stage-8-gallery\">